### `/authorize` processing flow

- `RequestValidator.validateAuthorizeRequest()` checks platform is in enum (CORE, NAP, VAP, LATAM, PIN)
- If platform is non-NAP, at least one of `caseNumber`, `merchantId`, `level4Entity` must be non-blank
- NAP requests pass the validator but are rejected at the service layer with HTTP 400 (`Platform is not supported`)
- iqorgid and iqentities JWT claims are extracted from the decoded JWT
- If both claims are blank, returns HTTP 403 with body `Token doesn't contain orgId & entities`
- caseNumber resolution: `WDP.CASE.findByCaseNumber()` returns `C_LEVEL1_ENTITY` (merchantId/levelEntity) and `C_LEVEL4_ENTITY` (chainId/level4Entity)
- The `findByCaseNumber()` call is OUTSIDE any try/catch — `DataAccessException` propagates uncaught to Spring Boot's default 500
- CH-type (chain-level) DB2 lookup is wrapped in `catch (Exception e)` — DB2 failures are silently caught, control falls through to the MT-type lookup
- MT-type (merchant-level) DB2 lookup is NOT inside a catch block — `DataAccessException` propagates uncaught to 500
- 200 with empty body = authorization granted (`ResponseEntity.status(HttpStatus.OK).build()`)
- 403 with JSON error body = denied
- Edge case: when authorizeToken() falls through to the catch block AND `levelEntity` is also blank, `isAuthorized` stays false but no exception is thrown — service returns HTTP 200 (silent authorization bypass)

